entry.title: The Enterprise Act 2002 (Mergers) (Interim Measures: Financial Penalties) (Determination of Control and Turnover) Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order makes provision, for the purposes of section 94A of the Enterprise Act 2002 (c. 40) (“the Enterprise Act”), for determining when an enterprise is to be treated as controlled by a person and for determining the turnover of an enterprise.

entry.title: The Government Resources and Accounts Act 2000 (Estimates and Accounts) Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order designates specified central government bodies in relation to named government departments for the purpose of those departments’ supply estimates and resource accounts.

entry.title: The Ukraine (European Union Financial Sanctions) Regulations 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision relating to the enforcement of Council Regulation (EC) No. No. 208/2014 dated 5 March 2014 (OJ L 66, 6.3.2014, p.1) concerning restrictive measures directed against certain persons, entities and bodies in view of the situation in Ukraine (“the Council Regulation”).

entry.title: The Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013 (Consequential and Contrary Provisions and Scotland) Order 2014

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013 (Consequential and Contrary Provisions and Scotland) Order 2014

entry.summary: This Order makes amendments to primary legislation as a consequence of the coming into force of the majority of the provisions of the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013 (c. 30) (“the Act”). The Order comes into force on 13th March 2014 (except for the provision made by paragraph 31 of Schedule 1 which comes into force on 3rd June 2014). A separate Order (the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013 (Consequential Provisions) Order 2014) making consequential amendments to subordinate legislation is also coming into force on 13th March 2014.

entry.title: The Inspectors of Education, Children’s Services and Skills (No. 2) Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order appoints the person named in the Schedule as Her Majesty’s Inspector of Education, Children’s Services and Skills.

entry.title: The Legislative Reform (Overseas Registration of Births and Deaths) Order 2014

ukm:Subject.Value: REGISTRATION OF BIRTHS, DEATHS, MARRIAGES ETC

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Legislative Reform (Overseas Registration of Births and Deaths) Order 2014

category.term: REGISTRATION OF BIRTHS, DEATHS, MARRIAGES ETC

entry.summary: This Order amends section 41 of the British Nationality Act 1981 which enables regulations to be made relating to the registration of births and deaths of persons who were born or who died in a country outside the United Kingdom.

entry.title: The Valuation (Telecommunications, Natural Gas and Water) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2014
entry.summary: The Valuation (Telecommunications, Natural Gas and Water) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010, (“the 2010 Regulations”), provide that certain hereditaments of any company listed in the Schedule to those Regulations shall, for the purposes of the Rates (Northern Ireland) Order 1977, be treated as a single hereditament occupied by that company.

entry.title: The Rates (Unoccupied Hereditaments) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend paragraph 2 of the Schedule to the Rates (Unoccupied Hereditaments) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011 (S.R. 2011 No. 36).

entry.title: The Prevention of Oil Pollution (Convention Countries) (Revocation) Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order revokes the Prevention of Oil Pollution (Convention Countries) Order 1981 (S.I. 1981/612) (“the 1981 Order”).

entry.title: The Taxes (Interest Rate) (Amendment) Regulations 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend regulation 5 of the Taxes (Interest Rate) Regulations 1989 (S.I. 1989/1297) (“the 1989 Regulations”).

entry.title: The CRC Energy Efficiency Scheme (Allocation of Allowances for Payment) (Amendment) Regulations 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the CRC Energy Efficiency Scheme (Allocation of Allowances for Payment) Regulations 2013 (S.I. 2013/3103).

entry.title: The Common Agricultural Policy Single Payment and Support Schemes (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Common Agricultural Policy Single Payment and Support Scheme Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010 (“the principal Regulations”). The principal Regulations make provision in Northern Ireland for the administration of Council Regulations (EC) No. 73/2009 (O.J. L30, 31.01.2009, p 16), and other associated Community instruments in relation to direct support schemes under the Common Agricultural Policy.

entry.title: The Recovery of Costs (Remand to Youth Detention Accommodation) (Amendment) Regulations 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Recovery of Costs (Remand to Youth Detention Accommodation) Regulations 2013 (S.I. 2013/507) by inserting new amounts which local authorities are liable to pay the Youth Justice Board for England and Wales in respect of each night on which a child is detained on remand in a young offender institution, a secure training centre or a secure children's home on or after 1st April 2014. In the case of secure children's homes, the Regulations also insert a new amount in respect of each night on which a child is detained on or after 1st May 2014.

entry.title: The Rates (Small Business Hereditament Relief) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2014
entry.summary: The Rates (Small Business Hereditament Relief) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010, as amended, provide for rate relief in respect of certain small business hereditaments for any financial year ending before 1st April 2015.

entry.title: The Consular Fees (Amendment) Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order further amends the Consular Fees Order 2012 to make amendments to fees in connection with passport applications. The Order reduces the fees for applications made overseas for adult and child 32 page passports, and for 48 page passports, except for Diplomatic, Official or Armed Forces passports.

entry.title: The National Health Service (Charges to Overseas Visitors) (Scotland) (Amendment) Regulations 2014
entry.summary: Regulation 5 of the National Health Service (Charges to Overseas Visitors) (Scotland) Regulations 1989 (“the 1989 Regulations”) exempts certain categories of overseas visitors from the requirement to pay for treatment the need for which arose during a visit to the United Kingdom. These Regulations amend regulation 5 to include within those categories of visitors who are taking part or involved in the Commonwealth Games 2014. It is anticipated that members of the Games Family will be in Scotland in the period from 7th July to 7th August 2014 inclusive for the Games.

entry.title: The General Osteopathic Council (Application for Registration and Fees) (Amendment) Rules Order of Council 2014
entry.summary: The Rules contained in the Schedule to this Order amend the General Osteopathic Council (Application for Registration and Fees) Rules as set out in the Schedule to the General Osteopathic Council (Application for Registration and Fees) Rules Order of Council 2000 (S.I. 2000/1038) by reducing, in certain circumstances, the “entry fee” payable by an Osteopath when first entered on to the register, by reducing the “retention fee” payable by an Osteopath in order to remain on the register subsequently, and by reducing the “restoration fee” payable by an Osteopath in order to have an entry restored to the register.

entry.title: The Tuberculosis (Scotland) Amendment Order 2014
entry.summary: This Order amends the Tuberculosis (Scotland) Order 2007 (“the 2007 Order”).

entry.title: The Housing Benefit (Habitual Residence) Amendment Regulations 2014
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Housing Benefit Regulations 2006 in relation to the definition of “person from abroad”.

entry.title: The Health Professions Council (Registration and Fees) (Amendment) Rules 2013 Order of Council 2014
entry.summary: This Order amends the Health Professions Council (Registration and Fees) Rules scheduled to the Health Professions Council (Registration and Fees) Rules Order of Council 2003 (S.I. 2003/1572) (“the 2003 Order”).
